node.text:
Prosecution On The Table For Former Uganda Airlines Management⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Uganda’s President Yoweri Museveni has ordered the dissolution of the board of directors for Uganda Airlines. The move comes following a widespread investigation that revealed issues of corruption, mismanagement, and collusion. President Museveni has ordered the IGG to consider prosecuting some of these officials.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠
⁠

node.text:
Lufthansa Sends An Airbus A340 To Help The Afghanistan Evacuation⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Lufthansa is helping to evacuate people from Afghanistan with one of its Airbus A340 aircraft. The German government has chartered the flights. The German flag carrier’s aircraft aren’t flying into Afghanistan but instead collecting people removed from the country to Qatar and Uzbekistan by the German military. ⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Vincenzo Pace | Simple Flying | @jfkjetsofficial⁠
⁠

node.text:
Airlines Predict Post-Pandemic Travel Boom Between China And Japan⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
This week, two owners of a joint-venture airline expressed their optimism for a post-pandemic tourism boom between Japan and China. The airline in question is Spring Airlines Japan, which is a collaboration between Chinese carrier Spring Airlines, and major Japanese carrier Japan Airlines.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Vincenzo Pace | Simple Flying | @jfkjetsofficial⁠

node.text:
Rabbit Strike In Germany Causes €1 Million In Boeing 737 Damages⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
An ETF Airways Boeing 737 has returned to service after sucking a rabbit into its engine upon landing in Bremen, Germany. The unfortunate incident has cost ETF Airways an incredible one million euros ($1,180,000). A McDonnell Douglas MD-82 and a Boeing 767 had to jump in to the rescue.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: IAC⁠
⁠

node.text:
640 People Cram Into A C-17 Leaving Afghanistan⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Amid chaotic scenes at Kabul’s Hamid Karzai International Airport, around 640 people have been evacuated from the city on a single United States Air Force (USAF) C-17A flight to Al Udeid Air Base airbase in Qatar. It is likely the most people ever carried on this type of plane.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠
⁠

node.text:
United Tells Flight Crew Not To Use Duct Tape On Passengers⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Recent high-profile disruption incidents have seen US carriers restrain abusive travelers with duct tape. This appears to have become a more common phenomenon since the ongoing global health crisis began. However, United is determined not to deploy such measures, and has instructed staff to refrain from taping abusive passengers to their seats.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Vincenzo Pace | Simple Flying | @jfkjetsofficial⁠
⁠

node.text:
Swiss Airline Helvetic Finishes Its Embraer Fleet Replacement⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Helvetic Airways has completed its ambitious fleet renewal project, with the final E195-E2 touching down in Switzerland on Sunday. The airline is currently the largest operator of the next generation Embraer jet, with eight E190-E2s and four E195-E2s in its fleet.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Helvetic Airways⁠
⁠

Emirates Rolls Out Special Airbus A380 Livery Celebrating The UAE 

✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️

Emirates has rolled out a special Airbus A380 livery to celebrate 50 years of the United Arab Emirates. The Airbus is one of a collection of aircraft from both the A380 and 777 families that are due to get the livery to recognize the country’s significant milestone. 

🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬

Photo Source: Emirates

One Month In: How Are Things At Brazilian Startup Airline ITA 

✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️

The new Brazilian airline startup, Itapemirim Transportes Aéreos, had 423 flights during its first month of services. Today, the carrier released its first monthly stats, and we can see how the company fared during its first weeks operating across Brazil.

node.text:
How Much Money Will The World’s Airlines Lose This Year? 

✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️

The outlook for the aviation industry at the start of the summer season was that airlines were on track for a $48 billion loss, or thereabouts. But as the year has progressed, we’ve seen green shoots of recovery in many markets around the world, notably in Asia and the USA. Has this changed the situation going forward? 

🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬

Photo Source: Vincenzo Pace - @jfkjetsofficial - Simple Flying
